<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3089] A component without ServicePermissions cannot be registered as a service</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3089</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given the following Component XML&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;scr:component immediate=&quot;true&quot; xmlns:scr=&quot;http://www.osgi.org/xmlns/scr/v1.1.0&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;implementation class=&quot;BindingImpl&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;reference&lt;br/&gt;
    bind=&quot;bind&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    unbind=&quot;unbind&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    policy=&quot;dynamic&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    cardinality=&quot;0..1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    interface=&quot;ServiceProvider&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;service&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;provide interface=&quot;Binding&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/service&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/scr:component&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When this component&apos;s bundle does not have ServicePermission&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ServiceProvider , GET&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, Binding is not registered as a service.&lt;br/&gt;
But I think that Binding can be registered.&lt;br/&gt;
Because the component&apos;s reference specifies optional cardinality.&lt;br/&gt;
(see OSGi Compendium R4.2&lt;br/&gt;
       112.3.2 Reference Cardinality, 112.9.1 Service Permissions)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
