                            <comment id="13092666" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2011 06:54:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed. I think this is this piece of code verifying dependencies:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if ( !dm.hasGetPermission() ) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                // bundle has no service get permission
**             satisfied = false;
            }
&lt;p&gt; else if ( !dm.isSatisfied() ) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                // bundle would have permission but there are not enough services
                satisfied = false;
            }

&lt;p&gt;At ** we should probably assume satisfaction if the reference is optional.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13092671" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2011 07:07:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in Rev. 1162659 by accepting an optional reference to which no permission is granted as satisifed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13125633" author="yasuk" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2011 06:52:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close issue, passed my tests using the revision. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
